'''[[苹果公司|苹果公司]]'''是一家专门负责生产[[电脑|电脑]]及[[手提電話|手提電話]]等消费类[[电子产品|电子产品]]及运营在线服务的[[美国|美国]][[跨国公司|跨国公司]]。尽管该公司享有盛名，惟其劳师动众的生产方式却惹来非议。苹果公司受到的诸多批评包括利用[[血汗工厂|血汗工厂]][[劳工|劳工]]<ref name="sweatshop1">{{citation |url=http://www.mailonsunday.co.uk/news/article-401234/The-stark-reality-iPods-Chinese-factories.html |title=The Stark Reality of iPod's Chinese Factories |work=Daily Mail |location=UK |date=2006-08-18 |accessdate=2014-10-01 |archive-date=2014-01-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140131115805/http://www.mailonsunday.co.uk/news/article-401234/The-stark-reality-iPods-Chinese-factories.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="sweatshop2">{{citation |last=Musgrove |first=Mike |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/06/15/AR2006061501898.html |title=Sweatshop Conditions at IPod Factory Reported |work=The Washington Post |date=2006-06-16}}</ref><ref name="sweatshop3">{{citation |last=Kahney |first=Leander |url=http://www.wired.com/gadgets/mac/commentary/cultofmac/2006/06/71138 |title=Judging Apple Sweatshop Charge |publisher=Wired |date=2006-06-13 |accessdate=2014-10-01 |archive-date=2013-02-09 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130209093307/www.wired.com/gadgets/mac/commentary/cultofmac/2006/06/71138 |dead-url=no }}</ref>、破坏环境、商业行为不道德，均为生产电子产品的方式所带来的后果。此外，该公司先前亦被批评打官司前，率先收集必要证据<ref>{{citation |last=Orlowski |first=Andrew |url=http://www.theregister.co.uk/2005/09/13/apple_thinksecret/ |title=Apple shot first, asked question later, say sued sites |publisher=The Register |date=2005-09-13}}</ref><ref>Flores, Marc, [http://www.mobilecrunch.com/2010/02/20/over-5000-apps-stricken-from-the-apple-app-store-new-rules-in-place/ Over 5000 apps stricken from the Apple app store, new rules in place], MobileCrunch, 2010-02-20</ref><ref>{{citation |last=Orlowski |first=Andrew |url=http://www.theregister.co.uk/2006/05/04/apple_sa_deep_links/ |title=Apple sues itself in the foot (again) |publisher=The Register |date=2006-05-03}}</ref>。

== 垄断及反竞争行动的指控 ==
苹果公司曾多次被不同國家的監管機構指控垄断市場及存在反竞争行动，當中包括美國、[[印度|印度]]<ref name="#1">{{Cite web|title=印度監管機構出手 初步認定蘋果公司違反反壟斷法|url=https://www.hk01.com/即時國際/718879/印度監管機構出手-初步認定蘋果公司違反反壟斷法|access-date=2022-05-17|date=2022-01-01|last=宛然|work=香港01|language=zh-HK}}</ref>、[[法国|法國]]<ref name="#2">{{Cite web|title=法國反壟斷機構對蘋果開出 11 億歐元罰單|url=https://technews.tw/2020/03/16/french-antitrust-body-fines-apple-1-1-billion-euros-for-anti-competitive-behavior/|access-date=2022-05-17|work=TechNews 科技新報|language=zh-TW}}</ref>、[[英国|英國]]<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=英國競爭與市場管理局認定Google、蘋果壟斷手機市場 可能造成價格上漲|url=https://udn.com/news/story/7098/5964723|access-date=2022-05-17|date=20211216T161343Z|last=聯合新聞網|work=聯合新聞網|language=zh-Hant-TW}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Apple and Google duopoly limits competition and choice|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/apple-and-google-duopoly-limits-competition-and-choice|access-date=2022-05-17|work=GOV.UK|language=en}}</ref>、[[欧洲联盟|歐盟]]<ref name="#3">{{Cite web|title=欧盟对苹果公司进行反垄断调查|url=https://chinese.aljazeera.net/technology/2020/6/17/欧盟对苹果公司进行反垄断调查|access-date=2022-05-17|work=chinese.aljazeera.net|language=zh-Hans}}</ref>、[[俄罗斯|俄羅斯]]<ref name=":2">{{Cite news|title=Russian watchdog says Apple abused mobile app market dominance|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-russia-apple-law-idUSKCN25622E|newspaper=Reuters|date=2020-08-10|accessdate=2022-05-17|language=en}}</ref>、[[波兰|波蘭]]<ref name=":3" />、[[荷兰|荷蘭]]<ref name="#4">{{Cite web|title=【反壟斷】荷蘭指控蘋果 App Store 違反競爭法，或面臨5000萬歐元罰款 - ezone.hk - 網絡生活 - 生活情報|url=https://ezone.ulifestyle.com.hk/article/3141223/%E3%80%90%E5%8F%8D%E5%A3%9F%E6%96%B7%E3%80%91%E8%8D%B7%E8%98%AD%E6%8C%87%E6%8E%A7%E8%98%8B%E6%9E%9C%20App%20Store%20%E9%81%95%E5%8F%8D%E7%AB%B6%E7%88%AD%E6%B3%95%EF%BC%8C%E6%88%96%E9%9D%A2%E8%87%A85000%E8%90%AC%E6%AD%90%E5%85%83%E7%BD%B0%E6%AC%BE|access-date=2022-05-17|work=ezone.hk 即時科技生活}}</ref>、[[意大利|義大利]]<ref name="#5">{{Cite web|title=義反壟斷裁罰 谷歌、蘋果各罰逾3億 - 自由財經|url=https://ec.ltn.com.tw/article/breakingnews/3749511|access-date=2022-05-17|date=2021-11-26|last=自由時報電子報|work=自由時報電子報}}</ref>、[[日本|日本]]<ref name="#6">{{Cite web|title=日本反壟斷監管機構全面審查蘋果和Google|url=https://www.hk01.com/即時國際/686150/日本反壟斷監管機構全面審查蘋果和google|access-date=2022-05-17|date=2021-10-08|last=宛然|work=香港01|language=zh-HK}}</ref>及[[大韩民国|韓國]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=蘋果與南韓反壟斷調查和解 將在明年於南韓成立開發者學院與製造研發協助中心|url=https://www.cool3c.com/article/166215|access-date=2022-05-17|date=2021-09-29|last=Yang|first=Mash|work=Cool3c}}</ref>。

=== 便携式设备 ===
苹果的便携式设备，无论是基于[[iOS|iOS]]的（即[[iPhone|iPhone]]、[[iPod_Touch|iPod Touch]]和[[iPad|iPad]]），或是其他非基于[[iOS|iOS]]的（即[[iPod_Classic|iPod Classic]]、[[iPod_Nano|iPod Nano]]和[[iPod_Shuffle|iPod Shuffle]]），均被批评捆绑[[iTunes|iTunes]]，让[[iTunes_Store|iTunes Store]]垄断这些设备<ref>{{citation|url=http://newsvote.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/technology/7002612.stm|title=Time for Apple to face the music?|publisher=BBC News|date=2007-09-19|first=Bill|last=Thompson}}</ref>。因此，[[史蒂夫·乔布斯|史蒂夫·乔布斯]]被勒令出席有关[[反垄断|反垄断]]行为的[[法庭聆讯|法庭聆讯]]，尤其是[[iPod|iPod]]和[[iTunes|iTunes]]<ref name="apple monopoly">{{cite web |url=http://www.coated.com/steve-jobs-ordered-to-attend-court-regarding-antitrust-case/ |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2011-03-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130119121640/http://www.coated.com/steve-jobs-ordered-to-attend-court-regarding-antitrust-case/ |archivedate=2013-01-19 }},</ref>。同样，苹果公司的[[FairPlay|FairPlay]]及其前身专有的[[无损压缩|无损格式]][[音频编码|音频编码]]格式——[[Apple_Lossless|Apple Lossless]]没有授权[[数字版权管理|数字版权管理]]，导致iTunes商店、iTunes电脑端的苹果无损编码及非iTunes来源购买的内容，不被其他制造商的设备运行<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/au/terms.html|title=Terms and Conditions|publisher=Apple|accessdate=2014-08-14}}</ref>。2009年4月，iTunes Store上的全部音乐不设数字版权管理<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.macworld.com/article/139879/2009/04/itunes.html|title=iTunes is DRM-free, adds variable pricing|publisher=Macworld|first=Jim|last=Dalrymple|date=2009-04-07|accessdate=2010-07-22}}</ref>，然而不适用于其他内容。独立反向工程编解码器ALAC被发布。2011年，苹果公司在[[Apache|Apache]]许可证下取得ALAC的源代码。

=== iTunes ===
因允许客户从任何成员国自由购买商品和服务，苹果公司的在线销售音乐在欧盟陷入的争议。iTunes透过客户付款明细中的发起国家信息，限制购买量，反过来迫使购买费用更高国家的消费者和其他iTunes音乐买家。2004年12月3日，英国公平贸易办事处向[[欧盟委员会|欧盟委员会]]申诉iTunes音乐商店违反欧盟自由贸易立法。苹果公司表示不相信违反欧盟法律，称被唱片公司和发行商授予的权利在法律上限制。《[[计算机世界|计算机世界]]》评论称，委员会的主要对象并非苹果公司，而是唱片公司和音乐版权机构。在国家合作的基础上，苹果把内容分发至各国商店时别无选择<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/130384/ |title=European Borders Fracture iTunes |publisher=PC World |first=Martyn |last=Williams |date=2007-04-04}}</ref>。
=== Google Voice的争议 ===
苹果一直被批评试图阻止iPhone用户使用[[Google_Voice|Google Voice]]。谷歌的应用程序一向被iPhone阻止，苹果声称其改变iPhone的预设功能，也就是说，谷歌的语音装置、语音邮件，不会传送到iPhone的原生程序，而非藉由谷歌应用的路由，因此“毁掉”iPhone的用户体验。这引起了iPhone开发者和用户的争议，[[美国联邦通信委员会|美国联邦通信委员会]]亦着手调查苹果不让用户由苹果在线商店安装Google Voice的决定<ref>{{citation |last=Kincaid |first=Jason |url=http://www.techcrunch.com/2009/07/31/fcc-takes-on-apple-and-att-over-google-voice-rejection/ |title=FCC Takes On Apple And AT&T Over Google Voice Rejection |publisher=TechCrunch |date=2009-07-31 |accessdate=2014-10-01 |archive-date=2018-04-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180403094838/https://techcrunch.com/2009/07/31/fcc-takes-on-apple-and-att-over-google-voice-rejection/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。到2010年11月，Google Voice推出iPhone版<ref>{{citation |last=Gassert |first=Patrick |url=http://www.techieinsider.com/news/4016 |title=Google Voice Arrives For The iPhone |publisher=Techie Insider}}</ref>。

=== Adobe Flash和iPhone OS的反垄断争议 ===
iOS 4.0 [[软件开发工具包|SDK]]发布后，苹果变更服务条款，禁止采用未经苹果批准的语言，编写iPhone程序。外界批评禁止使用[[Adobe_Flash|Adobe Flash]]和其他iPhone程序是反竞争行为。纽约时报援引一名Adobe员工，称该政策反竞争<ref>Adobe Systems' [http://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/796343/000079634310000007/form_10q.htm#riskfactors SEC filing] alleging expected loss of ability to compete in the market because of Apple's position on Flash on the iPhone and iPad, Form 10q, March 5, 2010.</ref><ref name="apple-slaps">{{citation |last=Brimelow |first=Lee |url=http://theflashblog.com/?p=1888 |title=Apple Slaps Developers In The Face |publisher=TheFlashBlog |date=2010-04-09}}</ref><ref>{{citation |last=Williams |first=Hank |url=http://whydoeseverythingsuck.com/2010/04/steve-jobs-has-just-gone-mad.html |title=Steve Jobs Has Just Gone Mad |publisher=Why does everything suck? |date=2010-04-08 |access-date=2014-10-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022224525/http://whydoeseverythingsuck.com/2010/04/steve-jobs-has-just-gone-mad.html |archive-date=2014-10-22 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{citation |last=Schonfeld |first=Erick |url=http://techcrunch.com/2010/04/09/is-steve-jobs-ignoring-history-or-trying-to-rewrite-it/ |title=Is Steve Jobs Ignoring History, Or Trying To Rewrite It? |publisher=TechCrunch |date=2010-04-09}}</ref>。2010年5月3日，[[Ars_Technica|Ars Technica]]和《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》报道[[联邦贸易委员会|联邦贸易委员会]]和[[美国司法部|美国司法部]]正决定哪些机构展开反垄断调查<ref>{{citation |last=Cheng |first=Jacqui |url=http://arstechnica.com/apple/news/2010/05/apples-compiler-policy-may-land-it-in-hot-water-with-ftc.ars |title=Apple iPhone OS compiler policy may lead to antitrust probe |publisher=Ars Technica |date=2010-05-03 |accessdate=2014-10-18 |archive-date=2011-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606150510/http://arstechnica.com/apple/news/2010/05/apples-compiler-policy-may-land-it-in-hot-water-with-ftc.ars |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{citation |last=Kosman |first=Josh |url=http://www.nypost.com/p/news/business/an_antitrust_app_buvCWcJdjFoLD5vBSkguGO |title=An antitrust app |work=The New York Post |date=2010-05-03}}</ref>。

2010年4月8日，约翰·格鲁伯在Daring Fireball博客发布名为《新版iPhone开发者协议禁止Adobe Flash在iPhone上使用》的文章，苹果公司随后修改了iPhone SDK许可协议的第3.3.1条款。反对苹果变更许可的声音迅速在博客和其他人身上蔓延<ref name="DaringFireball20100408">{{Cite web |url=http://daringfireball.net/2010/04/iphone_agreement_bans_flash_compiler |title=New iPhone Developer Agreement Bans the Use of Adobe's Flash-to-iPhone Compiler |accessdate=2014-10-18 |archive-date=2010-04-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100430123334/http://daringfireball.net/2010/04/iphone_agreement_bans_flash_compiler |dead-url=no }}</ref>，人们很快注意到，协议中的语言条款，也禁止[[MonoTouch|MonoTouch]]、[[Lua|Lua]]、[[Unity3D|Unity3D]]等开发工具。

原本的iPhone OS 3的3.3.1条款为：

发布应用程序只能使用苹果规定的[[API|API]]，不得使用或调用任何公开或私有的API<ref name="DaringFireball20100408" /><ref name="FactoryJoe">{{Cite web |url=http://factoryjoe.pbworks.com/iPhone-Developer-Program-License-Agreement |title=Original iPhone OS 3 Developer Program License Agreement |accessdate=2014-10-18 |archive-date=2010-06-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100613011635/http://factoryjoe.pbworks.com/iPhone-Developer-Program-License-Agreement |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

iPhone OS 4中的3.3.1条款被改成；

发布应用程序只能使用苹果规定的[[API|API]]，不得使用或调用任何为on公开或私有的API。应用程序起初必须以Objective-C、C、C++或执行iPhone OS Webkit的JavaScript语言编写，代码仅能用C、[[C++|C++]]编写，Objective-C需可编译，直接链入API的文档（禁止应用程序透过中介编译、[[兼容层|兼容层]]和工具链入API）<ref name="DaringFireball20100408" />。

史蒂夫·乔布斯发布了一份回应，题为《对Flash的想法》<ref name="ThoughtsOnFlash">{{Cite web |url=https://www.apple.com/hotnews/thoughts-on-flash/ |title=Thoughts on Flash |accessdate=2014-10-18 |archive-date=2017-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170108151300/http://www.apple.com/hotnews/thoughts-on-flash/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，他在此文章中专门针对[[Adobe|Adobe]]公司的[[Flash|Flash]]平台发表评论，而对其他第三方开发平台和工具绝口不提。文章<ref name="ThoughtsOnFlash" />迅速引发外界对史蒂夫·乔布斯严厉的批评，他被许多人指责公开撒谎<ref name="JobsLiesInThoughtsOnFlash">[http://www.blixtsystems.com/2010/04/jobs-lies-in-thoughts-on-flash/ Jobs Lies in Thoughts on Flash]</ref><ref name="DecodingSteveJobsDressingDownOfFlash">[http://techcrunch.com/2010/04/29/steve-jobs-apple-adobe-flash/ Decoding Steve Jobs' Dressing Down Of Flash]</ref><ref name="SteveJobsIsLyingAboutFlash">[http://www.businessinsider.com/steve-jobs-is-lying-about-flash-2010-4 Steve Jobs Is Lying About Flash]</ref><ref name="SteveJobsOnFlashCorrectingTheLies">{{Cite web |url=http://jessewarden.com/2010/04/steve-jobs-on-flash-correcting-the-lies.html |title=Steve Jobs on Flash: Correcting the Lies |access-date=2014-10-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141212014113/http://jessewarden.com/2010/04/steve-jobs-on-flash-correcting-the-lies.html |archive-date=2014-12-12 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。乔布斯断言Flash是不开源、封闭和专用的，吸引针对开源项目的大量关注，为Adobe制作Flash的开放给开发者的指引创造优势<ref name="ListOfOpenSourceFlashProjects">{{Cite web |url=http://osflash.org/open_source_flash_projects |title=List of open source projects built on the open Adobe Flash specification |access-date=2014-10-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141022035818/http://osflash.org/open_source_flash_projects |archive-date=2014-10-22 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

=== 勾结唱片公司 ===
2015年5月，据报道[[美国司法部|美国司法部]]和[[联邦贸易委员会|联邦贸易委员会]]开始调查苹果[[垄断利益集团|垄断]]主要唱片厂牌利益，阻止他们提供靠广告支撑的免费音乐流媒体服务，为重新上线的{{le|Beats Music|Beats Music}}订阅服务吸收用户。重要的是，苹果公司据称要求唱片公司将音乐从竞争对手[[Spotify|Spotify]]（降低了苹果音乐销售营收的服务）的免费增值服务中下架，并且向[[环球音乐|环球音乐]]集团支付了和该唱片公司在YouTube上相等的版权费，换取其歌曲从Spotify下架<ref name="recode-applemusicfree">{{cite web|title=Big Music Labels Want to Make Free Music Hard to Get, and Apple Says They’re Right|url=http://recode.net/2015/03/06/big-music-labels-want-to-make-free-music-hard-to-get-and-apple-says-theyre-right/|website=Re/code|accessdate=2015-05-06}}</ref><ref name="verge-freemusiccollusion">{{cite web|title=Apple pushing music labels to kill free Spotify streaming ahead of Beats relaunch|url=https://www.theverge.com/2015/5/4/8540935/apple-labels-spotify-streaming|website=The Verge|accessdate=2015-05-06|archive-date=2015-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150507000759/http://www.theverge.com/2015/5/4/8540935/apple-labels-spotify-streaming|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

=== App Store交易费用及壟斷性 ===
App Store提供的iOS应用的内购或会员资格需要使用iTunes支付系统购买，苹果会从交易费用中抽取30%<ref>{{cite web |first=David |last=Chartier |title=Apple launches long-awaited subscriptions for App Store |url=https://www.macworld.com/article/1157927/app_store_subscriptions.html |website=Macworld |publisher=International Data Group |date=2011-02-15 |accessdate=2017-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171207013925/https://www.macworld.com/article/1157927/app_store_subscriptions.html |archive-date=2017-12-07 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。相比信用卡公司通常收取的1-5%的利润<ref>{{cite web |first=Matt |last=Assay |title=Death by 30% cut: Apple app tax must change |url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2011/02/18/the_payment_problem/ |website=The Register |publisher=Situation Publishing |date=2011-02-18 |accessdate=2017-12-06}}</ref>和部分在线市场收取的1-10%，
该政策被批造成每笔交易费用高昂<ref>{{cite web |first=Jay |last=Yarow |title=How Apple's Decision To Collect 30% Of Every iOS App Sale Could Lead To Its Downfall |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/apples-ios-tax-2013-4 |website=Business Insider |publisher=Axel Springer SE |date=2013-04-18 |accessdate=2017-12-06}}</ref>。

2015年7月，音乐流媒体服务Spotify向iOS订阅户发送电子邮件，要求他们取消App Store订阅，等待过期，然后登陆Spotify网站注册会员，绕过App Store收取的30%交易费用，使服务更实惠<ref>{{cite web |first=Chris |last=Welch |title=Spotify urges iPhone customers to stop paying through Apple's App Store |url=https://www.theverge.com/2015/7/8/8913105/spotify-apple-app-store-email |website=The Verge |publisher=Vox Media |date=2015-07-08 |accessdate=2017-12-06 |archive-date=2019-09-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190928030015/https://www.theverge.com/2015/7/8/8913105/spotify-apple-app-store-email |dead-url=no }}</ref>。约一年后，《{{le|Recode|Recode}}》报道，Spotify总法律顾问{{le|霍拉西奥·古铁雷兹|Horacio Gutierrez}}致函苹果时任法律总顾问{{le|布鲁斯·休厄尔|Bruce Sewell}}，称该苹果不准Spotify应用更新，“对Spotify及其客户造成严重损害”。出于“商业模式规则”，苹果不批准新版本，要求Spotify如果“希望使用应用横须获取新用户和销售订阅”，必须使用iTunes支付系统。古铁雷斯严厉批评这一连串的事件，写道：“最新的事件引起对美国和欧盟竞争法的严重关切，苹果继续采取令人不安的模式排除矮化Spotify在iOS上的竞争力，成为苹果音乐的对手，特别是在苹果此前针对Spotify的反竞争行为背景下。”他还将App Store的审核流程辟为“危害竞争对手的武器<ref>{{cite web |first=Peter |last=Kafka |title=Spotify says Apple won’t approve a new version of its app because it doesn’t want competition for Apple Music |url=https://www.recode.net/2016/6/30/12067578/spotify-apple-app-store-rejection |website=Recode |publisher=Vox Media |date=2016-06-30 |accessdate=2017-12-06}}</ref>。”在[[BuzzFeed|BuzzFeed]]公开的回信中，布鲁斯·休厄尔表示：“我们发现问题是你们要求我们豁免适用于所有开发者的规则，把我们的服务公开诉诸谣言和部分事实陈述。”他补充道：“我们的指南平等地适用于所有应用开发者，不论他们是游戏开发商、电子书销售商、视频流媒体服务，还是数字音乐分销商；不论他们是否和苹果竞争。”他进一步声称公司推出自家的苹果音乐流媒体服务时，“没有改变我们的行为或规则”，苹果没有没有任何行为来支持反竞争主张<ref>{{cite web |first=John |last=Paczkowski |title=Apple Slams Spotify For Asking For “Preferential Treatment” |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/johnpaczkowski/apple-fires-back-at-spotify-for-asking-for-preferential-trea |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160701215735/https://www.buzzfeed.com/johnpaczkowski/apple-fires-back-at-spotify-for-asking-for-preferential-trea |website=BuzzFeed |date=2016-07-01 |archivedate=2016-07-01 |accessdate=2017-12-06}}</ref>。《{{le|天才少年报|Boy Genius Report}}》的扎克·爱普斯坦（{{lang|en|Zach Epstein}}）认为Spotify非常生气，“它不是非营利机构”，没有在其他公司服务的基础上免费开放他们的应用，并总结出一个夸张的结论：“显然苹果不应该补偿Spotify，让他们获得数千万潜在用户”<ref>{{cite web |first=Zach |last=Epstein |title=Spotify is furious at Apple because it’s not a non-profit |url=http://bgr.com/2016/06/30/spotify-vs-apple-anti-competitive-app-store/ |website=BGR |publisher=Penske Media Corporation |date=2016-06-30 |accessdate=2017-12-06}}</ref>。

2016年8月，Spotify开始“惩治”向苹果音乐提供独家版权的艺人，削弱他们作品在服务中的显著地位，减少提供宣传机会<ref>{{cite web |first=Juli |last=Clover |title=Spotify Punishing Artists Who Offer Apple Music Exclusives [Updated] |url=https://www.macrumors.com/2016/08/26/spotify-punishing-apple-music-exclusive-artists/ |website=MacRumors |date=2016-08-26 |accessdate=2017-12-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171212031443/https://www.macrumors.com/2016/08/26/spotify-punishing-apple-music-exclusive-artists/ |archive-date=2017-12-12 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Jordan |last=Kahn |title=Report: Spotify punishing artists that take Apple Music exclusives by limiting promotion (Update: Spotify denies) |url=https://9to5mac.com/2016/08/26/spotify-apple-music-exclusives/ |website=9to5Mac |date=2016-08-26 |accessdate=2017-12-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171214014827/https://9to5mac.com/2016/08/26/spotify-apple-music-exclusives/ |archive-date=2017-12-14 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。2017年5月，《[[金融时报_(英国)|金融时报]]》报道Spotify联合其他几家公司致函欧盟，声称“某些”操作系统、应用商店和搜索引擎从“网关”和“看门人”的“特权地位”<ref>{{cite web |first=Chance |last=Miller |title=Spotify again accuses Apple of abusing its size & acting as a ‘gatekeeper’ |url=https://9to5mac.com/2017/05/06/spotify-again-accuses-apple-of-abusing-its-size-acting-as-a-gatekeeper/ |website=9to5Mac |date=2017-05-06 |accessdate=2017-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170914125940/https://9to5mac.com/2017/05/06/spotify-again-accuses-apple-of-abusing-its-size-acting-as-a-gatekeeper/ |archive-date=2017-09-14 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。几天后，[[路透社|路透社]]报道欧盟正在制定新的法律法规，处理大公司和小企业之间的冲突，特别是“贸易不公手段”方面<ref>{{cite web |first=Julia |last=Fioretti |title=EU to tackle complaints over tech companies' trading practices |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-eu-digital/eu-to-tackle-complaints-over-tech-companies-trading-practices-idUSKBN18614K |website=Reuters |publisher=Thomson Reuters |date=2017-05-10 |accessdate=2017-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Ben |last=Lovejoy |title=EU planning a new law addressing ‘unfair contractual clauses’ following Spotify’s complaint against Apple |url=https://9to5mac.com/2017/05/10/eu-apple-spotify-complaint/ |website=9to5Mac |date=2017-05-10 |accessdate=2017-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516215828/https://9to5mac.com/2017/05/10/eu-apple-spotify-complaint/ |archive-date=2017-05-16 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。于2017年12月发出的另一封信再度指责苹果“经常滥用”自己的立场，要求监管机构介入并“确保‘公平竞争’”<ref>{{cite web |first=Ben |last=Popper |title=Spotify and Deezer ask EU regulators to stop Apple from abusing its dominance |url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/12/13/16773806/spotify-deezer-eu-regulators-apple |website=The Verge |publisher=Vox Media |date=2017-12-13 |accessdate=2017-12-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Chance |last=Miller |title=Spotify again attacks Apple for its gatekeeper-like policies |url=https://9to5mac.com/2017/12/13/spotify-apple-gatekeeper/ |website=9to5Mac |date=2017-12-13 |accessdate=2017-12-14}}</ref>。

2020年6月16日，歐盟针对苹果公司的Apple Store和Apple Pay进行两项反垄断调查，称苹果公司的行为违反了合法商业竞争，這案源起自瑞典音乐流服务商[[Spotify|Spotify]]向欧盟状告苹果以不公平方式限制竞争对手。<ref name="#3"/>欧盟竞争委员会的韦斯塔格（Margrethe Vestager）在2021年4月的一份声明中表示：“我们的初步调查结果是：苹果违反了欧盟竞争法。”<ref>{{Cite web|title=欧盟控苹果违反竞争法 {{!}} DW {{!}} 30.04.2021|url=https://www.dw.com/zh/%E6%AC%A7%E7%9B%9F%E6%8E%A7%E8%8B%B9%E6%9E%9C%E8%BF%9D%E5%8F%8D%E7%AB%9E%E4%BA%89%E6%B3%95/a-57391278|access-date=2022-05-17|last=Welle (www.dw.com)|first=Deutsche|work=DW.COM|language=zh-CN}}</ref>2022年3月25日，歐盟通過《數碼市場法案》，針對總值達750億歐元、年銷售額達750億歐元及最少有4,500萬名每月用戶的企業，需要提供第三方支付系統、第三方搜索引擎及可以刪讓用戶刪除裝置上預設的應用程式。<ref>{{Cite web|title=歐盟對Google及蘋果等巨企 祭反壟斷措施|url=https://hk.on.cc/hk/bkn/cnt/intnews/20220326/bkn-20220326020031401-0326_00992_001.html|access-date=2022-05-17|date=2022-03-26|work=on.cc東網|language=zh-hk}}</ref>2022年5月2日，歐盟正式就Apple Pay技術向蘋果提反壟斷起訴。<ref>{{Cite web|title=歐盟正式就Apple Pay技術向蘋果提反壟斷起訴 (19:13) - 20220502 - 即時財經新聞|url=https://finance.mingpao.com/fin/instantf/20220502/1651490175538/%e6%ad%90%e7%9b%9f%e6%ad%a3%e5%bc%8f%e5%b0%b1apple-pay%e6%8a%80%e8%a1%93%e5%90%91%e8%98%8b%e6%9e%9c%e6%8f%90%e5%8f%8d%e5%a3%9f%e6%96%b7%e8%b5%b7%e8%a8%b4|access-date=2022-05-17|work=明報財經網|language=en}}</ref>

